node.text:
@juliannamargulies is my new co- star on @themorningshow and now I can safely say, a dear friend! 😁 So I was thrilled to hear that she shared her fascinating life in a new memoir. Join us as we discuss many topics including: 
-her international childhood 
-her early career woes 
-how she learned to leave situations that no longer served her 
-how George Clooney gave her some of the best news of her life! 

Check it out! #sunshinegirl

node.title: What a life this woman has lived! ☀️

node.text: All right, here are the facts: this book is every suspense-lovers dream and it kept me up WAY too late turning pages. 😱 Our August @reesesbookclub pick, #WeWereNeverHere by @andibartz is a novel with crazy twists and turns that will have you ditching your Friday night plans for more chapters. The story centers around two friends, Emily and Kristin, who love to go on adventures around the world. This year they are in Chile and through a series of circumstances, end up in a room with a dead body… but here’s the twist, it’s not the first time it has happened to them!  Coincidence? You'll just have to pick up a copy to find out.... 📚🤫

node.text: What a tremendous day! ☀️ I started @HelloSunshine to change the way all women are seen in media. Over the past few years, we have watched our mission thrive through books, TV, film and social platforms. Today, we’re taking a huge step forward by partnering with @blackstone, which will enable us to tell even more entertaining, impactful and illuminating stories about women’s lives globally. 💫 I couldn’t be more excited about what this means for our future.  I am committed to continuing to create opportunity for filmmakers, authors and creators of all backgrounds and experiences to tell their stories in their own way, and reach more audiences who will see that their stories matter. ☀️ I am deeply proud of the team that got us to this incredible moment, and I’m thrilled to be working with @blackstone, Kevin Mayer and Tom Staggs to grow a next generation media company. They are committed to helping our mission to empower women and the people who celebrate them. One story at a time.

node.text: Did you know cancer is the second leading cause of death in the U.S. and the leading cause in Canada? Together, we have the power to change that and save more lives. On August 21st at 8pm ET/PT and 7pm CT, I’m proud to join @SU2C as an Executive Producer for their televised fundraising event! Join us for a special evening as we Stand Up with one goal in mind: to make every cancer patient a long-term survivor. Learn more at StandUpToCancer.org/Show. #StandUpToCancer

node.text: I’ve said it once and I’ll say it again… I LOVE historical fiction. It might be my favorite genre but shhh don’t tell the others. 🤫 My @reesesbookclub Late Summer YA pick is no exception! The Downstairs Girl by @staceyleeauthor is clever, poignant and funny. It’s a bold portrait about a young Chinese-American woman named Jo who is faced with adversity and the realities of intersectionality in her community. As an anonymous writer in a local newspaper, this young woman is able to use her voice for greater good. Such a charming, yet timely & important story – pick up a copy of #TheDownstairsGirl and follow along at @ReesesBookClub. 📚
